Adds a new `module-alias` tiddler field that allows JavaScript library tiddlers to declare one or more short names for use with `require()`.

Plugin developers can now write:

```
module-alias: prosemirror-model
```

on a library tiddler at `$:/plugins/myplugin/lib/prosemirror-model.js`, and any JavaScript module inside that plugin can then call:

```javascript
const {Node} = require("prosemirror-model");
```

instead of the full tiddler path. This resolves the problem described in [[issue #8999|https://github.com/TiddlyWiki/TiddlyWiki5/issues/8999]].

Notes:

* The field value uses the same string-array format as `tags` (space-separated; use `[[double brackets]]` for names containing spaces)
* Real module titles always take priority over aliases
* Duplicate alias warnings are logged to the console


Adds a new `alias` tiddler field (string array format, same as `tags`/`list`) that allows a tiddler to declare one or more alternative names.

Aliases work across all layers of TiddlyWiki:

* ''require()'': `require('short-name')` resolves to a library tiddler with `alias: short-name`, enabling npm-style package names for plugin libraries
* ''Links'': `[[short-name]]` displays as a resolved (non-missing) link and navigates to the real tiddler; alias links receive a `tc-tiddlylink-alias` CSS class
* ''Navigation'': any `tm-navigate` message with an alias as target (including from action widgets) is resolved to the real tiddler before opening in the story river
* ''Transclude'': `{{short-name}}` and `<$transclude $tiddler="short-name"/>` transclude the content of the aliased tiddler
* ''Backlinks'': `[backlinks[RealTitle]]` includes tiddlers that link via any declared alias
* ''Backtranscludes'': `[backtranscludes[RealTitle]]` includes tiddlers that transclude via any declared alias
* ''Missing titles'': links via alias are not counted as missing tiddlers
* ''Filter operator'': `[alias[short-name]]` returns tiddlers that declare the given alias (uses the new AliasIndexer for efficient lookup)

Real tiddler titles always take priority over aliases. See [[GithubLinks PR #8999|https://github.com/TiddlyWiki/TiddlyWiki5/issues/8999]] for the original request.
